</link><description>Good people of New York, please join me November 14 at the 92nd St. Y, where I'll be talking on stage with Donald Johanson about the fiftieth anniversary of Lucy's discovery--and what we've learned about human evolution in the half-century since. Details here: &lt;a href="https://www.92ny.org/event/dr-donald-johanson-and-carl-zimmer?mcSID=1031480" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" translate="no"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://www.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="ellipsis"&gt;92ny.org/event/dr-donald-johan&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;son-and-carl-zimmer?mcSID=1031480&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a href="https://files.mastodon.social/media_attachments/files/112/956/667/950/342/556/original/6b3ad63e758f7890.jpg"&gt;&lt;img src="https://files.mastodon.social/media_attachments/files/112/956/667/950/342/556/original/6b3ad63e758f7890.jpg" alt="Mastodon image" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">112956655825587492</guid><pubDate>Tue, 13 Aug 2024 20:43:04 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Carl Zimmer</title><link>https://mastodon.social/@Carl_Zimmer/112956669105179703</link><description>Photo by Jason Kuffer &lt;a href="https://flic.kr/p/6FAH6C" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" translate="no"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=""&gt;flic.kr/p/6FAH6C&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">112956669105179703</guid><pubDate>Tue, 13 Aug 2024 20:46:27 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Carl T. Bergstrom</title><link>https://fediscience.org/@ct_bergstrom/112957271680731046</link><description>Taylorism is a management philosophy based on using scientific optimization to maximize labor productivity and economic efficiency. Here's the result of making the false Taylorist assumption that the output of scientific research is scientific papers—the more, faster, and cheaper, the better.&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a href="https://files.mastodon.social/cache/media_attachments/files/112/957/271/904/708/443/original/d6272ea2bc89ee0c.png"&gt;&lt;img src="https://files.mastodon.social/cache/media_attachments/files/112/957/271/904/708/443/original/d6272ea2bc89ee0c.png" alt="Mastodon image" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">112959176015421339</guid><pubDate>Wed, 14 Aug 2024 07:23:59 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Dorothy Bishop</title><link>https://mastodon.social/@deevybee/112947884733874910</link><description>For those who missed it: René Aquarius reports on his experience of trying to be a diligent reviewer for MDPI.  Seems they don't like it, and find ways to publish the paper anyway.&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a href="http://deevybee.blogspot.com/2024/08/guest-post-my-experience-as-reviewer.html" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" translate="no"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;http://&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="ellipsis"&gt;deevybee.blogspot.com/2024/08/&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;guest-post-my-experience-as-reviewer.html&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;Coupled with this trend, &lt;a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/s11192-024-05125-w" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" translate="no"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="ellipsis"&gt;doi.org/10.1007/s11192-024-051&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;25-w&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, suggests peer review is not working at &lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://mastodon.social/tags/MDPI" rel="tag"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;MDPI&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;br/&gt;&lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://mastodon.social/tags/publishing" rel="tag"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;publishing&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://mastodon.social/tags/peerreview" rel="tag"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;peerreview&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">112959815951760979</guid><pubDate>Wed, 14 Aug 2024 10:06:44 +00